	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm a level 22 Wizard and alot of us complain that our spells resists too much despite the fact that Wiz spells are the least resistible among all casters, by how much is just a mystery.<br><br>Against red cons, we can just forget about it. Resists, resists, resists...<br><br>The other night I was in a 6 people group. 2 monks, 2 druids, 1 enchanter and 1 wiz.&nbsp;&nbsp;We were taking things down fast, yellows and white cons.  All my spells were consistently hitting for full even against the yellows which would normally do some partial resists.<br><br>Then a red con was pulled.  Normally I would sit out or get up and whack with my staff since it's a waste of manna since it'll only resists.  But I was at full manna so what the heck.  <br><br>I casted stun and it stuck.. stunned it again and it stuck... hmmm. What the heck, with the mob hitpoint halfway down, I used my best DD at this point... Bam... hit for full... 174 points of Damage.  A red con turned it's back after that and was beaten to death by the monks.<br><br>So I did a "/g All my spells were hitting that red one. Never happened before"<br><br>Then a response, "I was opening up with Tash on it... it lowers it's magic resistance, that's why you're hitting it for full."<br><br>My jaw dropped.  So this is Verant's fix to the Wiz resist problem that they won't tell us. It's the Enchanter.  I wanted to get up and hug that Chanter.  Also wanted to ask him if he was a Verant programmer who wanted to show one wizzie that the Wizard is a balanced class.<br><br>That night in that group, I was master of Damage.  I would cast 3 stuns and a Force Shock.  Out of the 3 damagers in there, me and 2 monks, I was accountable for at least 38% of direct damage. That would leave 68% in between the 2 monks which comes down to 34% each. With my 3 stuns, they were probably getting an additional 5% each of free hits on the mob.  So I could easily be attributed to 48% damage including damage incurred while mob is stunned. I could do more damage but I would never cast more than 4 times per fight to avoid going oom and what fun is it if the monks can't do their nice roundhouses and flying kicks.  Chanter gave me breeze as well so I was giving my 38% for each mob.  The Druids didn't involve themselves much in the fights since they focused there strategy on healing the 2 monks.<br><br>It was a fun night.  The best night I've had in EQ so far.  Makes me feel like I don't want to group with anyone anymore unless there is a Chanter opening up with Tash.<br><br>So all you whiny wizards out there who complain about resists.  Verant has fixed it!  They want you to be grouped with an Enchanter.  PERIOD.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
