	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 23rd 11:44 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i agree 100% with the above.&nbsp;&nbsp;in the end (for those of us that hold out) it's the wizzies that make or brake the campaign/quest/whatever.  i can remember the days when people in groups would yell at me for not engaging in melee (oh i wonder where they are now, dead probably).  <br><br>CASTING TIPS For the Newbies at early levels 1 - 20:<br><br>Soloing?  very brave & noble.  <br>DO NOT engage in combat unless you're near 100%hp & 70%mana. you'd be surprised (even at lvls 10-14) how a skelly or zombie can waste you. <br><br>HIT only single MOBs that con blue and have potential to drop good loot.  pay attention to the auctions and see what items are hot.  often folks'll pay HUGE amounts for what the merchants give you jack for. <br><br>Get Direct Dmg spells as soon as you level.  also, YOU MUST HAVE the following when attainable: Gate, Fade (for getting better at Alt, trust me on this), Root, Shadowstep, & Bind Affinity.<br><br>While Grouping:<br>DO NOT NUKE until the MOB is at least 50% down.  reason?  nothing like 5 MOBs beating your ass since you just hit them once for 78 points of damage.  remember FIFTY%.  if a tank complains and asks you to do sooner suggest that he play a caster and find out what happens himself.  often these folks have no clue that 5-10 hits will kill you at levels under 20.<br><br>DO NOT USE AREA EFFECT unless insturcted to do so by an experienced group member.  reasons, see above.  these spells are good only in emergencies or at higher levels.  in any case, they often take too long cast and you'll never pull it off while being directly hit by several MOBs.  try ShadowStep instead and then run your butt off.  sure it's a wussie thing to do, but... you live and keep your precious xp.  <br><br>IF YOU SEE YOUR TANK RUN, try Rooting the individual culprit MOB.  then nuke ONLY after you see the MOB has "adhered to the ground".  your tank will love you for this.  <br><br>IF YOU KNOW your party candle take the MOB without your help AND they're in excellent heatlh, let them.  save your mana and always be sitting (medding when possible)<br><br>REMEMBER, at low levels, XP is your main concern, not tweaks and fancy clothing.  sure these help and if you've got some cash, then hey, buy em.  otherwise, just stay alive and get your skills up.  when you reach higher levels, the items you DO GET will make the one's you're thinking of now about as worthless as spider legs.  kind of like a mutual fund:  you're in for the long haul investment.  (if you see anyone under 20 carrying around reallly nice stuff, don't fret, SOMEONE GAVE IT TO THEM.  THEY DID NOT QUEST THE ITEM THEMSELVES).  <br><br>with that in hand, good luck, cast well, and see you in the planes someday where everyone begs at our feet like the  D O G S  T H E Y  A R E.<br><br>{X}:-/&gt;<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
