	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98832136212112><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98832136212112>RE: Wizards not nerfed</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98832136212112#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=829><span id= >Nakano</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 26th 5:42 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>this is an extremely narrow view of the wizard class, and one which causes most wizards to get bored quickly. The reality is that if you know what you're doing, the wizard is one of the most flexible classes, but its important to know under what situations to use which spells.<br><br>AE IS NOT USELESS<br>say it with me now... AE can be one THE most powerful ability of our class, no question.&nbsp;&nbsp;I always have to feel sorry for the wizards I encounter whom haven't bothered to aquire their AE spells and have stuck with just their shock line all through their lives. Talk about a boring way to play! below are some strategies that use AE extremely sucessfully and I urge all wizards to expriment with.<br><br>AE rains: these are basically the wizard's version of a DOT, and even though they are often resisted, they are low-agro damage, so if you get a single pull you can cast one of these when the mob is at 80% health and then sit back down to meditate until its below 50 without worry about being agroed on. This not only does a signifcant amount of damage to the mob, but it can go a long way toward showing your group that you're actually doing something and not just sitting around.<br><br>AE Columns/pillars: These are truely the bread&butter of the wizard class, and which really set us apart from other classes. druids get some good AE spells like these, but not until later levels are they anywhere near as efficent as this line of spells, and they allow us to quad-kite, one of the fastest ways to level in the game. Quad-kiting often as seen as hideously dangerous, but this is simply not the case. starting at lvl 24 you can quad-kite quite easily in Lake of Ill Omen just by bumming a sow from the local druid or shaman, without evening having to worry about snare. And not only is quad-kiting alot of xp, its also quite a rush. ;) I quad-kited from 24-30 with little difficulty, and I think in that time I only died once, and that was because of linkdeath. <br><br>AE columns and pillars also have their place in groups, for crowd control. I know what you're thinking, usually AEs are anti-crowd control, but this doesn't have to be the case. Often in the sarnak fort of Lake of Ill Omen and the Giant Fort of Frontier Mountains, if we got two and didn't have an enchanter, I'll wait until the tanks knock down one of the mobs to about 80%, then start laying in with column of lightning, which I can usually get 2 casts off with before the 2nd, untouched mob will agro on me. at which point I can either kite it around or root it until the first is dead. With leatherskin up, this isn't nearly as dangerous as it sounds.<br><br>PBAE: While at my low level of 30 I haven't had much chance to play with these, graffe's site provides detailed walkthroughs on how to setup the fastest xp group in norath.. the AE group post 50. I've heard first-hand accounts of multi-wizard groups downing 20(!!) or more mobs at a time, with no deaths.. I think it more people under 50 were willing to try AE tactics, you could do this below 50 as well.<br><br>Al'kabor's AE: okay, these AE's *do* suck. hopefully someday verant will fix them.<br><br>In closing, a good wizard can be a lot more to a group than just an evacer and minor damage dealer. be flexible and react to situations that arrive intelligently, and expirment with your spells.. many of them have applications you might not expect. We're wizards after all, smarter is part of our job description. ;)<br><br>-Chirko<br>&nbsp;<br>-Nakano K'shynn<br>lvl 54 Cleric of Innoruuk<br>-Chiriko,<br>lvl 30 Wizard<br>Innoruuk Server<br>Silent Just</td></tr>
