	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 18th 11:19 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Starting a new wizard now-a-day isn't that tough.&nbsp;&nbsp;With all the info provided on the web, now, you should be able to start the "perfect" wizard.  First, what's important...INT.  No, INT is not the most important stat to have early (lvls 1 thru 40).  For example start an Agnostic Dark Elf Wizard.  Work your bonus points so that you have no more than 115 INT.  Add to get about 100 or 105 STA and put the rest in AGI.  Wizards need HPs.  The more Stamina, the more HPs.  INT = mana, but with all the items found thus far in EQ, mana items give more than INT in the early stage.  Grab some moonstone rings (30-50p each), black chitin legs (100p) and some other low level mana-giving items and that should hold you through mid-life.  At 29, learn how to kite mobs with your snare.  No JBoots?, buy SOW potions (10 dose potions go for 100p each).  Learn the zones, Shout from zone to zone asking what lvls fight here.  Don't be afraid to ask questions.  There are plenty 50+ characters out there that's been where you are and will be willing to help.  I started a wizard (myself) and I'm absolutely in love with this class.  At 48 now (12 days of Total Time playing), I have 194 INT, 110 STA and that setup gives me 1100 Hps (with Arch Shielding) and about 2300 mana (INT + mana gear).  I only solo, group rarely, and love it.  Wizards are a very good class to play.  Just don't get wrapped up in "I gotta have INT.", INT will come, hell I don't have Freeti Boots yet and when I do, it'll put me at 203!  So don't think we're nerfed, we're not, just learn how to play and you'll have a blast.<br>&nbsp;<br>Wihangia Atchoboof<br>54th Channeler of Fennin Ro</td></tr>
