	   <tr><td colspan=2>Everyone knows that every character has its plus and minus. Im a lvl 14 Wizzie and is also going through growing pains suddenly. It took me only 2 weeks to lvl from 1 to 13, but it also took me 2 weeks to get from 13 to 14, and things arent going any faster at 14 either. I finally realized that we as Wizards have chosen a character that requires more brains than bronze to advance at certain levels. "WHERE AND HOW YOU FIGHT" seems to be the best ways for wizzies to advance during certain harder levels. You can melee and blast your way to lvl 13, but you'll find out that it doesnt work effectively beyond 13 (or 12 for some). I was "only" able to advance from 13 to 14 by using the root and blast technique. I believe a wizard can advance effective if you use your intelligence...your head. After all, isnt INT the important criteria for wizards? Unlike a warrior who doesnt need to change his/her fighting strategy can easily slash and bash their way into higher lvls than wizzies stuck in their teens, ever noticed that most of the higher lvl people in EQ in their 50's are mostly blasters such as Wizard? I havent gotten there yet, but I do believe that fighters cans easily advance in earlier stages, but blasters will survive the higher stages. There might be some 50 plus lvl pure fighters out there but most 50 plus people I've came across have magical powers of some type. I've read that a lvl 60 Wizard can do between 1500 to 2000 per blast in a few seconds. If that isnt worth fighting for, than pick up a sword. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
