	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am confused by this question, are you asking skill points when creating your wizard, or skill points when training at your guildmaster?<br>When creating your wizard I would suggest putting most if not all of your points into intelligence. Intelligence equals mana and mana is the wizards best friend. After all they arent the best melee class in the game. =)<br>For guildmaster training you will find that research is a pain and will take up most of your training points in order to become a master at it(that is if you decide to research instead of buying those researched spells).<br><br>Hope this helps a little, didn't clearly understand the question.<br><br>~Cayahsis Aspensadow<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
