	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 12th 2:51 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello Level 8 Wiz.<br><br>It doesn't really matter what spells you put in your 8 slots as long as you have your most powerful mem'd up.&nbsp;&nbsp;At this levels, manna is best saved for blasting.  Root and nuke won't come into it's own until level 12.  The reasoning for this is because you should still be able to survive meleeing the mobs if you run out of manna. And your shock spells cast fast enough and does serious damage for same level monsters while you melee. Just as long as you got em softened up with your lvl 8 long distance nukes.  It's good to study a monsters melee pattern when meleeing, that way you'll know when to fire off that shock spell to avoid interrupts.<br><br>Avoid root at this level.  One resist or if it doesn't hold long enough and you'll be out of manna and you'll be running to the guards or dead. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
