	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a gnome Mage and when i was lvl 2 i left Steam Front. There just werent enough friendly ppl. The best place i recommend to u are Human cities such as Qeynos and Freeport. Iv been to both. Both cities are the in the same concidering the newbie zone is right infrnt of the town. Then u move out and fight in the very next zone. I recommened Freeport though. When u move out of the newbie zone in Freeport u go into EC with the one of the biggest trading zones in the world. In EC there are animals roaming around that are lvls 3-7. then there are orc camps at lvl 9-11 u can fight those. then when u hit lvl 12 go into North Ro with is in the next zone after EC. (you go through the Ec Tunnel which u cant miss, thats where ppl trade). In North ro at lvl 12 Fight at dervish cutthroat camps with zome others.(the dervs will range from lvls 11-14 or so). MAke sure u pull creatures from just outside the derv camps. This is excatley what i did. I lvled fast. And sometimes in North Ro solo sometimes, remember ur a mage and have a pet u should be able to hit lvl 14 or so fighting dervs. Then u go to Oasis in the next zone right after North Ro thats when u fight Orcs at orc highway. Most of the orcs are lvl 13 and 14. Watch out for Specre though they are lvl 30's and the Sand giants but ppl will warn everyone to run if they come near the shores. After this its up to you were to go to. Probably South Karana Which ISN'T near East Commons or anythign. Good luck with your jorney.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
